      ## Findings, and the updated design

      5/7 participants understood that “What's nearby” was for adding places to the map. But some participants thought that places would only be shown near the selected hotel.

      So Joy Kordts, UX Writer at trivago, decided to change the copy of the button to “Explore this area”. To make it clearer that you’re searching for places within the visible map area. Not just near the selected hotel.

